cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles north of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: moving north, then forecast to turn north-northeast and track parallel to the west coast of Florida before making a turn toward Apalachee Bay and then moving inland across the southeast United States
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or over Apalachee Bay, Florida

weather_observation.watch_coast: Englewood FL northward to Suwannee River FL; Cuban provinces of La Habana, Artemisa, Mayabeque, Pinar del Rio, and the Isle of Youth
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Keys, south and west coasts of Florida, and the northeast Gulf Coast from Tampa Bay to Apalachee Bay
weather_observation.wind: Minimal winds expected; tropical-storm-force winds unlikely at the port
weather_observation.rainfall: Light to moderate rain possible late week as remnants pass well to the south and west
